lzh_formatted:
  title: 梅
  author: 姜希孟
  language: lzh
  text: 黃昏籬落見橫枝。緩步尋香到水湄。千載羅浮一輪月。至今來照夢醒時。
korean:
  title: 매
  author: 강희맹
  language: kor
  text: |-
    황혼의 울타리에 비스듬한 가지 보고
    느린 걸음으로 향기를 찾아 물가에 이르렀다
    천재의 나부의 한 수레바퀴 달이
    지금에도 꿈 깰 때면 와서 비춘다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1450_020_0260&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Plum Blossom
  author: Kang Hee-maeng
  language: eng
  text: |-
    At dusk I glimpse the angled branch beyond the fence.
    With measured steps I follow fragrance to the water's edge.
    A thousand years—the moon above Luofu's plum trees,
    still comes to illuminate the moment when dreams awaken.
  footnotes:
    - Luofu (羅浮) refers to Mount Luofu in southern China, renowned in classical literature as a place of plum blossoms and immortal dwelling. The reference evokes the timeless quality of natural beauty transcending ages.
